{"id":"321571058_Phylogenetics_of_Indo-European_Language_Families_via_an_Algebro-Geometric_Analysis_of_Their_Syntactic_Structures","abstract":"Using Phylogenetic Algebraic Geometry, we analyze computationally the phylogenetic tree of subfamilies of the Indo-European language family, using data of syntactic structures. The two main sources of syntactic data are the SSWL database and Longobardi's recent data of syntactic parameters. We compute phylogenetic invariants and likelihood functions for two sets of Germanic languages, a set of Romance languages, a set of Slavic languages and a set of early Indo-European languages, and we compare the results with what is known through historical linguistics.","authors":["Kevin Shu","Andrew Ortegaray","Robert Berwick","Matilde Marcolli"],"meta":["December 2021Mathematics in Computer Science 15(2)","DOI:10.1007/s11786-021-00507-2"],"references":["324481029_Learning_implicational_models_of_universal_grammar_parameters","324055272_Heat_Kernel_Analysis_of_Syntactic_Structures","308807290_Syntactic_Structures_and_Code_Parameters","349585241_The_Theory_of_Principles_and_Parameters","345882316_The_Minimalist_Program","332087355_ReCombinatorics_The_Algorithmics_of_Ancestral_Recombination_Graphs_and_Explicit_Phylogenetic_Networks","326031082_Computational_phylogenetics_An_introduction_to_designing_methods_for_phylogeny_estimation","325387496_Syntactic_Phylogenetic_Trees","320589290_Prevalence_and_Recoverability_of_Syntactic_Parameters_in_Sparse_Distributed_Memories","319394257_Syntax_An_International_Handbook_of_Contemporary_Research","299999008_Syntactic_Parameters_and_a_Coding_Theory_Perspective_on_Entropy_and_Complexity_of_Language_Families","292148654_Correlated_Evolution_or_Not_Phylogenetic_linguistics_with_syntactic_cognacy_and_phonetic_data","290495259_The_Indo-European_controversy_Facts_and_fallacies_in_historical_linguistics","287971278_Maximum_Likelihood_for_Matrices_with_Rank_Constraints","283117600_Prevalence_and_recoverabil